# Match Kaggle Competitions to the Team

Read `/output/input.json`:
- `steps.fetch_competitions.competitions[]` — `{ ref, title, deadline, category, reward, description }` for open competitions.
- `steps.collect_profiles.profiles[]` — `{ userId, email, strengths, weaknesses, interests, currentLoad }` per team member.

## Task
Rank the competitions by fit with the team's collective strengths and interests, and against feasibility given their weaknesses and current load. Produce a shortlist of the best 3-5 as selectable options. For each option, explain the fit in the `description`.

## Output contract (MANDATORY)
1. Write the result JSON to `/output/result.json` using bash.
2. Your FINAL message must be ONLY: {"output_file": "/output/result.json", "summary": "..."}

Result JSON shape:
```json
{
  "options": [
    {
      "label": "<competition title>",
      "description": "<why it fits the team>",
      "value": { "competitionRef": "<ref>", "title": "<title>", "deadline": "<deadline>", "category": "<category>" }
    }
  ],
  "summary": "<one-line summary of the shortlist>"
}
```
Use only competitions present in the input. Do not invent refs.
